707413f-a.folder: Willow St. & Poplar St., Brooklyn, NY

706304f-a.text:
Poplar Street, west from Willow Street to Columbia Heights, where itterminates. The 3-story house, in the center, is on the latter street. In the background is the lower Manhattan skyline, the buildings (fror left to right) being the City Bank Farmers Trust, the Bank of
Manhattan and the 60 Wall Tower.
About 1939
Gift of Dr. Michael Wishengrad, A. R. P. S.
706304f-a.folder: Poplar Street & Willow Street, Brooklyn, NY

706308f-a.text:
32-34 Poplar Street, south side, between Willow and Hicks Streets, as
seen from Mc Eenney Street.
April 4, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.

707412f-b.text:

April 4, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same; showing only Nos. 1-3 Willow Street, with Poplar Street,
south side, east from Willow to Hicks Streets.
April 4, 1932.
